      • getAlertOrHeartbeat

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Object> getAlertOrHeartbeat()
        Gets the value of the alertOrHeartbeat property. This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the alertOrHeartbeat property. For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 
         getAlertOrHeartbeat().add(newItem);
        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list Alert Heartbeat
